div1.p: In the District Court holding terms at Seattle King County Washington Territory.
In re application of Alfred Woods for a writ of habeas corpus

On reading and filing the petition of Alfred Woods duly signed and verified by him, whereby it appears that he is illegally imprisoned and restrained of his liberty by John H. McGraw at the county jail in the City of Seattle, King County, Washington Territory, and stating wherein the illegality consists, from which it appears to me that a writ of habeas corpus ought to issue, wherefore His ordered that a writ of habeas corpus issued out of and under thee the seal of the District Court of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory holding terms at Seattle in said King county directed to the said John H. McGraw, commanding him to have the body of the body of the said Alfred Woods

before me, in the court room of said court, on Tuesday the 27th day of OCtober 1885 at 9:30 o'clock a. m. of that day to do and recieve waht shall then and there be considered concerning the said Alfred Woods, together with the time and cause of his detention and that he then and there have the said writ.

And it is further ordered that the said applicant Alfred Woods be allowed to prosecute this application in forma pauperis and without cost or expense to himself. Dated this 24th day of October 1885
Enter Seavey

4669 In District Court No 4669
In re application of Alfred Woods for writ of habeas corpus
Order Granting Writ
FILED OCT 24 1885 James Seavey, Clerk. by James P Ludlow Deputy Clerk.
J H McGraw
